snippet.textDisplay: Am I wrong for thinking that she has no right to be doing videos at this time? It actually makes me cringe. I know the justice system says we’re innocent until proven guilty, but when I saw her dressed and posed for crew pictures...she knows she’s not a crew member and there’s only so far being naive like “I didn’t know why I was doing this” can only take you. How could she not know what she was doing was wrong? She is not someone I would want for girls to look up to and be taking advice from...especially if she wants to play the dumb card!!! I have so many more passionate feelings about Olivia Jade posting videos, but I don’t want to get mean. That never solves anything. I understand she says how much she misses and is passionate about filming videos, but am I wrong for thinking she lost that right. I know some YouTubers are just characters, but the ones who document as themselves should have some sort of a moral compass and be a positive role model and unfortunately at this time she is just not. I may be wrong, but I feel like here presenting herself is selfish and self serving on so many levels (especially to her Mother). Olivia Jade- Stop posting YouTube videos and really go to school or get a real job to channel your “passion” and become a person that people can respect and feel good about letting the young females in their life to look to as a role model. I know being a YouTuber is very hard work for most people, but I’m sorry that I feel YouTube is a lazy short cut for you to avoid actually having to work hard.
